The word ‘state’ appeared in the Turkic languages from ancient times. Over time, it has come to designate an organized sociopolitical system with a system of law and agreed positions keepers of the societal peace. As a phenomenon, the state comprehensively covers all aspects of human life, including economics, law and military defence.

The classical dictionary of D.Ho tohkary (1912) defines the word for the first time as the activity of public management based on rights and duties of haci-musta’, that is, its milk mannlicher’s maximum orders (situa farsida).
